<p>I am trying to load a asp.net mvc 4 page with images in jpg extension as the img src. When requesting the images, it's automatically adding a forward slash to the url parameter resulting in a 400 (bad request) from server. How can I get around this?</p>  <p>Example (x.ImageUrl is definitely a string without the trailing slash):</p>  <pre><code>@foreach (var x in Model.List)     {         &lt;tr&gt;             &lt;td&gt;                 &lt;img src=@x.ImageUrl/&gt;&lt;/td&gt;             &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href="@x.ItemUrl"&gt;@x.Title&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;             &lt;td&gt;@x.Price&lt;/td&gt;         &lt;/tr&gt;     } </code></pre>  <p>In view images are requested like this:     <a href="http://ecx.images-amazon.com/images/I/51a6DHwbx-L._AA160_.jpg/" rel="nofollow">http://ecx.images-amazon.com/images/I/51a6DHwbx-L.<em>AA160</em>.jpg/</a></p>